review_text: good reviews don‚Äôt even do justice for how good Khao-So-I is. The food is excellent, the environment is lively and lovely. The restaurant is so busy but staff are so attentive!! Staff make excellent recommendation of dishes without upselling their more expensive dishes or anything. We‚Äôve had other Khao Soi, including Michelin guided shops but this is the best one for me and my husband. This may not be your everyday Khao Soi. We are tourists here and here to enjoy & experience things !! Worth every penny.

This seemed like a fusion take on khao soi, and overall it was great. The khao soi was very spicy and cover the taste of shrimp and scallops. but the staff were extremely caring when he noticed I was sweating and can‚Äôt handle with the spicy, he proactively offered extra coconut milk and pork broth to mellow the soup. However, the yogurt dessert‚Äôs texture was too hard and not creamy enough. If you can handle the spicy soup, you might want to skip dessert at a khao soi restaurant üòÜ

We came to Khao-S≈ç-i to try the typical and traditional dish of Chiang Mai. I ate the Khao-soi with Braised Beef. Here you can choose to have your dish with spicy curry broth (traditional version), or you to have stir-fried noodles without broth and therefore not spicy. Before choosing, the waitress was very kind as she brought me a small bowl with a taste of the broth, so I could taste and understand how spicy it was. In the end, I chose to have it in soup format with broth and diluted it with coconut milk to tone down the spiciness. We ate very well, it‚Äôs a must-try dish to try if you are in Chiang Mai.

The best fusion Khao Soi in Chiangmai, great atmosphere like old town Tokyo, very organised. Go early the best way is no queue and ending with soft ice cream, same quality as it in Tokyo. Don‚Äôt miss! üòÜ

A premium Khao Soi restaurant where the flavor is quite balanced, making it suitable for tourists to try. Honestly, the taste is pretty good, but personally, I prefer more local style places. That‚Äôs just my personal preference, so it wouldn‚Äôt be fair to judge the restaurant based on that. I recommend trying it yourself. Overall, it‚Äôs a good place definitely worth a visit if you‚Äôve never had Khao Soi before.
One of best Khao Soi we have in Thailand. Food and ambience are good. The staff attending to us are superb and attentive. Highly recommended to try them out when you are in Chiangmai.

I visited in the morning when it wasn't busy, and the staff were friendly, providing me with recommendations. It's a must-visit if you're in Chiang Mai; the food and atmosphere are great, making it feel like I was in Japan. The food was incredible, delicious, and authentically Northern Thai with a hint of Japanese fusion.
Aoffy was so lovely, the food was incredible and such a beautiful setting. I‚Äôll definitely come back here again. The dumplings were so juicy ans the Khao soi with thai sausage was amazing!!

Khao-S≈ç-i offers an exceptional dining experience that stands out even in a city renowned for its culinary delights. The restaurant‚Äôs signature Khao Soi dish features a rich, creamy curry broth with a perfect balance of spices, complemented by tender meat and a combination of soft and crispy egg noodles and delicious dumplings. This harmonious blend of textures and flavors creates a memorable meal that captures the essence of Northern Thai cuisine. Beyond the food, Khao-S≈ç-i can be praised for its cozy and clean ambiance, as well as its attentive and friendly service. The toilet, though, needs fixing and renovation. Apart from that, the staff‚Äôs dedication to providing a welcoming atmosphere increases the overall dining experience, making everyone feel valued and comfortable. Whether you‚Äôre a resident or a traveler exploring Chiang Mai, Khao-S≈ç-i is a must-visit destination for an authentic and satisfying meal. There‚Äôs also a dessert section, where you can relax after your meal and choose from a selection of hot and cold drinks, cream caramel, tiramisu, and a Japanese dessert. All in all, it has been a great experience. I have wanted to try this restaurant, and I am very pleased to do so. If I don't visit again, I will miss the friendly staff.

Khao-S≈ç-i takes the classic Northern Thai dish to the next level with their impressive Khao Soi 2.0 menu. Every dish is creative yet authentic, with a perfect balance of flavors that highlight the best of Japanese culture and Northern Thai cuisine. Truly one of a kind! The venue itself is nice, clean, and photogenic ‚Äì great for both foodies and anyone who loves sharing their dining experiences. Prices are very reasonable for the quality you get, and the restaurant is clearly well managed. Add to that a spacious parking area and professional, attentive staff, and you‚Äôve got the full package. Totally loving this place ‚Äì and without a doubt, I‚Äôll be coming back. A must-visit when in Chiang Mai! üçú

A very good place for enjoying delicious Khao Soi. The price of Khao Soi is higher than local shops, but it's definitely worth for the food, service and cozy atmosphere. For vegetarian, there are only one option, the tofu Khao Soi. Without the chili paste, the Khao Soi itself is not very spicy. You can add as much chili as you like. The ice cream (mixed) is yummy üòã

The khao soi was really tasty, rich broth and soft noodles with great flavor. The beef was tender and the portion was just right. Service was quick and friendly, and the place has a nice local vibe that makes it comfortable to sit and enjoy the food. Definitely worth trying if you‚Äôre around the area.

Disappointing given the prices. Opted for the more premium Tajima Aus Khao Soi beef thinking it would be nice and tender. I could have stayed there chewing it all day and not gotten very far. Despite being the only ones there the order was wrong to what we marked on the order sheet but I was glad I got a small instead of medium in the end. Dumpling were nice. Chicken Khao Soi was good too. The place is nice and presentation also but not good value for money

My first time in Chiang Mai, and this place becoming my first meal here. I ordered Khao So I with Braised Beef and Beef Tendon size small with soup and mineral water. The place not big, not too crowd (so many foreigner, didnt see local there), easy to get seat. My order came fast, it really curry but not too spices. The small size look small, but its okay for me. You can add the coconut milk, chili flakes, vegetable and/or lime inside, but without all of that, the soup still yummy. Lime made it more fresh, i suggest u pour it. The meat was juicy and tender, but the meat portion not so many, but you can add topping. The staff also nice, can speak english, you can pay with QR.

Khao soi with premium touch, but still worth to try. Food taste good , but the dine in area is a bit packed! Waiting list is long but you can capture some photos at the alley with japanese theme there. Worth to try!

Khao-S≈ç-i is hands down the best spot for Khao Soi in Chiang Mai! üçú The beef Khao Soi is absolutely delicious, rich, creamy, and full of flavor that keeps you coming back for more. üòã If you‚Äôre feeling adventurous, try the lobster Khao Soi ü¶û, it‚Äôs a bit pricey but totally worth it for a special treat. The taste is unique and will definitely impress your taste buds! The restaurant‚Äôs interior is beautiful and full of rich cultural vibes, making your meal feel even more special. üé®‚ú® It‚Äôs a hidden gem perfect for friends to enjoy together. You won‚Äôt regret giving it a try! üëç
Thank you, Jenny from Phayao hahaha the service is absolutely fantastic, food is tasty but you cannot choose the spicy level in soups so be prepared for that. The butterfly drink is delicious.

went to the restaurant and the cafe, this is my first time having khao so and this one set the bar for every khao so i tried after. I'd say this the best one i've tried so far, the flavor of the coconut and curry sauce is so rich. It's lowkey spicy for me without even adding the chili flakes. Matcha soft serve is standard but the honeybun is so good !
Very picturesque place decorated in traditional Japanese style. Food is delicious. Also the staff is extremely friendly and welcoming

I had a wonderful dining experience at Khao So I! The star of the show was definitely their signature Khao Soi ‚Äî rich, creamy curry broth with tender beef and perfectly cooked egg noodles. The dish came with all the essential condiments: pickled mustard greens, red onions, fresh herbs, and crispy noodles ‚Äî beautifully presented and thoughtfully portioned. The attention to detail was impressive, from the handcrafted ceramic dishes to the warm wooden tray that added a rustic charm. You can tell they care about both flavor and presentation. The ambiance was cozy and intimate, perfect for a relaxed meal with friends or a solo comfort food fix. Service was friendly and attentive. If you‚Äôre craving authentic Northern Thai cuisine in KL (or wherever you‚Äôre located), Khao So I is a must-visit. I‚Äôll definitely be back to try more from their menu!

Personally I feel it‚Äôs overrated, especially given the price. I ordered the small portion and it‚Äôs something like 240 baht. The problem is that 1. It‚Äôs definitely not enough for a male adult 2. I actually asked the server if it‚Äôs enough, and they recommended me the small portion 3. There‚Äôs really nothing special about the Khao so. The meat is indeed better than most random food stands, but that‚Äôs pretty much it 4. In fact, I felt a bit overwhelmed after the meal. Perhaps it‚Äôs that I‚Äôm just not a big fan of Khao soi. Still, this place is worth checking out, but not a must for sure

So delicious. Must visit! Recommend the beef tendon and shank soup dishes. We have also tried the pork fried rice. Matcha soft serve is so yummy! But they close down the machine around 7:30-8 pm or so. Order early! Note: ‚Ä¢ if you do not like spicy, get the dry noodles and ask for no spice. All soup based noodle dishes will be spicy. ‚Ä¢ if you require gluten free options, they do provide gluten free noodles but you must ask! The GF noodles were almost just as good as the original. I was very impressed.

The atmosphere and food blew me away! Very accessible to those who might not be as tolerant to spice, but preserves the authentic taste of northern Thailand who those who can with a Japanese twist. The service is spectacular, no notes. The atmosphere is very reminiscent of traditional Japan aesthetics and there are many cute photo opportunities in the area. The attention to detail is incredible, down to the fish themed cutlery. 100/10 would come back again
Great food. I tried beef khao soi and the meat was tender and tasty. Dumplings are very delicious. Red syrup tea also eases the spiciness of soup. There are also photogenic spots. Highly recommended.

Excellent food. Honestly the best meal we had in Chiang Mai, maybe even all of Thailand. The spice level was perfect and easy to titrate to your own level. Perfectly balanced flavors. Both the entrees we ordered were spectacular (one soup and one stir-fried). Wish we could come back but, sadly, this is our last day here. Til next time. Also, definitely try the soft serve. I usually don't like matcha, but it was the perfect way to cool us down.

Excellent!!! So good I wanna cry hahaha the curry taste so balance, savory with freshness of the lime juice‚Ä¶chef torched the lobster, it is so fresh the Australian wagyu topping is also amazing I add 2 more portion. The service is also excellent, friendly, and prompt response‚Ä¶Definitely will comeback!

Khao Soi with a twist of modern. Sweet and savory with choice of meats, but I recommend beef shank and tender. Services are perfect with courtesy and a friendly smile. Air condition room with wooden tables and chairs. Feels of authentic Thai sitting style with a/c.

The restaurant was packed with mostly tourists üòÜ We were curious of the Khao Soi noodle soup but aren‚Äôt really fans of chili or spicy food. We were contemplating if we should give it a try and the lovely staff was nice enough to give us a taste of the soup and to our surprise it‚Äôs way too much for us so we opted for the stir fry khao soi instead. Very tasty I love how tender the pork ribs üòã but we‚Äôre kinda disappointed they don‚Äôt have the milder version of soup (like some sort of spicy level options) The matcha soft serve was really good it‚Äôs a must try üòä

During my recent visit to Chiang Mai, I had the pleasure of stopping by Khao-S≈ç-i for a late lunch, and it truly exceeded my expectations. I opted for the beef shank khao soi, and I can honestly say it was one of the best dishes I‚Äôve had. The broth was incredibly rich and flavorful, perfectly balanced with a hint of spice that didn‚Äôt overwhelm the palate. The beef shank was cooked to perfection‚Äîtender and melt-in-your-mouth delicious. To complement my meal, I chose the butterfly pea tea, which was a delightful addition. Its natural sweetness paired beautifully with the savory khao soi, creating a harmonious dining experience. One notable feature was the helpful instructional card provided for those unfamiliar with how to enjoy khao soi. This thoughtful touch made the experience even more enjoyable and accessible to both locals and tourists alike. I also want to highlight the exemplary service from Aoffy, the hostess. She was incredibly kind and sweet, making sure I felt welcomed and comfortable. She spoke very good English, which made our conversation easy and enjoyable. Her initiative to chat with me when she noticed I was traveling alone added a warm and personal touch to my visit. Overall, Khao-S≈ç-i offers not just delicious food but also a wonderful atmosphere and friendly service. I would highly recommend it to anyone visiting Chiang Mai. Whether you're a khao soi aficionado or trying it for the first time, this place is a must-visit!

Very good restaurant. All staff very friendly and helpful. Specially Toa Billy . Good English and very professional. Potential staff . Billy good attitude and good hospitality. Excellent service . Toa good recommendation when presenting the menu . My family and I very enjoy the dinner tonight . Will suggest to my friends and guests also .

the staffs are really nice, they can speak both great english and mandarin, we chatted with the staff a bit, and she explained the menu and helped us order, also to make sure we can take the heat of the khao so i, so she gave us the broth to try before ordering, that's super thoughtful and caring but i didn't get to ask her name, but i think she's super friendly, she even shared her own experience working with p peach pachara with me after knowing i'm a big fan of his ü§£ it's not a restaurant only tourists visit, but there's also many thai people eating, which means the flavor is also good for the locals we had khao soi with beef tongue, khao soi with braised beef and beef tendon, nam prik noom fired rice with fried pork, they all tasted so good! and they kind of performed a bit with the fried rice, like shaping it beside our table, which is super cool and fun to watch for drinks, we had jasmine green tea and chysanthemum tea, the green tea is unsweetened, both of them can refill, it's great bc you might have to cool down the spiciness with the iced drink!

Food: The food was fantastic, with a great variety of meat and seafood. The lobster was a standout, and the soup was incredibly delicious. The ingredients were fresh, and they even offered unlimited vegetables for refill. I requested extra fish sauce, and they happily provided it. Service: The presentation was impressive, and the chefs maintained a clean and organized environment. The staff delivered quick, professional service, making the experience even better. Atmosphere: The atmosphere was excellent‚Äîclean, well-organized, and inviting. Additional Touches: The story behind how the restaurant was created is truly inspiring. It‚Äôs also worth noting that the restaurant attracts quality customers from around the world.

Loved it! The broth was incredibly rich and flavourful, and the meat was very tender, making each bite super satisfying. The portions of meat were also quite generous compared to other Khao Soi places. The service was attentive and warm-they help you choose the right Khao Soi for you, and even explain how to properly enjoy it, which really elevates the whole experience.

The vegetarian Khao Soi with fried tofu was incredible! Rich, creamy curry broth with just the right amount of spice, and the tofu was perfectly crispy on the outside while soft inside. It was packed with flavour and so comforting!! The staff were so friendly and accommodating ‚Äî they made sure everything was just right. Easily one of the best vegetarian meals I‚Äôve had in Chiang Mai. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a delicious meat-free option that doesn‚Äôt compromise on taste! And don‚Äôt forget to finish with their soft serve matcha ice cream!

We had dinner at Khao‚ÄëS≈ç‚Äëi in Chiang Mai and it felt more like dining in a stylish Japanese noodle house than at a typical Thai khao soi joint. The atmosphere was sleek, calm and the open kitchen added a fun energy, watching the chefs prepare each bowl was a highlight. The khao soi itself was delicious, creamy, richly spiced broth, tender meat and perfectly cooked noodles. It‚Äôs more refined than street-style versions yet still deeply comforting. Service was professional and friendly. They even provide refillable drinks The place is almost always busy, which makes sense given the quality and clean, inviting decor. There‚Äôs a modern, elevated feel without being pretentious. Must have: Get the classic chicken khao soi. Rich, balanced and highly satisfying. Highly recommend if you‚Äôre in Chiang Mai and want a polished take on the city‚Äôs iconic noodle soup.

Went to this place as this was suggested. I had the stir-fry noodles and it did not disappoint. You can request to not make it spicy, which I did. All the flavors go so well with the meat is is definitely a must-try!

It‚Äôs gimmick or (photogenic? )and a bit pricey for the decor. As a tourist, if you want to try Khao soi, I would recommend you to any other local one which is more authentic and at reasonable price. The noodles is so so and the chicken as well. BTW, the chef comes to your table if you order fried rice which makes the indoor having a bit strong kitchen fumes.
The famous Khao Soi with wagyu meat served in Japanese style! I really loved what we got. The restaurant is nice and cozy. We went at night and there was no line!

I think this is the best restaurant ive visited in chiang mai. The food tastes excellent, price wise ok, ambience ok, all's good! Totally highlight of my day here‚ù§Ô∏è order the one that I took pic, ebi + gyoza and the crunchy noodle (?) wassss epic

Excellent dining experience, very friendly staff and beautiful place. Noodles with beef was excellent value, but I felt the lobster was not the best value for money. Perhaps should have went for the gyoza instead. I‚Äôd still highly recommend the restaurant!
The food is excellent the server assisted us on how to place our order and instructions on how to eat khao soi. The ambiance of s also great üëçüèº
Went with my partner absolutely loved the food everything on our plates was delicious, cant wait for them to open in London. Must try the matcha ice cream was incredible

I came here with my boyfriend. We ordered different things and we both loved it!! So tasty! They also let me taste my soup beforehand to decide if it was too spicy for me üòä The atmosphere is also nice and the service as well. I'd definitely recommend coming here.

The food, staff and facilities are perfect. We opted to eat here two days in a row as we all loved it that much. I can‚Äôt say enough about the food other than everything was perfectly balanced and spiced so impressive !!

The good: * Shank & chuck eye beef khao soi soup was very good * The noodles were very nice * They certainly put a lot of effort into the place ‚Äì it‚Äôs cute and efficient despite the crowd The bad: * Meat arrives cold, which is fine when you mix it into a hot soup, but I don‚Äôt recommend the dry version * The chicken wasn‚Äôt great ‚Äì I‚Äôve had much better at a 40 baht chicken rice shop * The ice jasmine tea costs 49+tax and tastes just like water * Pricey in general and they add 10% on top
Beautiful places. Nice customer services. And foods are good and delicious. Aoffy was the waitress who served us and helped us to enjoy the foods. Recommended reastaurant.

I got the best ever Khao-soi from Khao-So-I (Yes, the name of this restaurant is really confusing üòÇ) The broth is really thick and creamy, strong flavour of coconut cream. The spicy is just perfect for me. The braised beef are soft and tasty. The chuck eye is just boiled, soft but not much flavor The shrimp and Hotate is so fresh and perfect cook, I wonder how the chef can cook so so nice. Very impressive. The chair is not so comfortable to eat, coz it's quite high compare to the table, so you need to bend down qhen eating. There is a girl with beautiful eyes promoted us with Mat ha ice-cream to kill the spicy on our tongue, really nice and smoothy and creamy, strong flavor of Matcha Perfect dinner ever in Chiang Mai.

It‚Äôs a Michelin. So expect to pay high prices. However, the food did not disappoint. Best Khao soi I‚Äôve had. You can choose from many different meats such as pork, beef, and seafood. The flavors were deliciously balanced creating a symphony of delight. Do note though, if you can‚Äôt tolerate spice, you can only have the ‚Äústir fried‚Äù version of the dish, not the soup. This is because the way they prepare the broth I believe. Could be a deal breaker for some. But my friend had the stir fried and she said it was also very good. In addition we shared fried tofu and the dumplings both of which were a treat. Worth the money üëçüèº

Probably going to be my favorite Khao Soi place from now on. The traditional taste of Khao SOI is still here but they made their dishes in a very innovative and creative way. Mimi, one of the waitresses was very attentive and welcoming to us customers. Very hard working and courteous. It made my dining experience much much nicer, I took her suggestion for the Khao Soi dumpling! it was really worth trying. It was a busy day when I came in, but the staff were super diligent with follow ups and not needing to be reminded repeatedly. The front line chefs were entertaining to watch. Very clean place and very nice atmosphere to be in! Would recommend for both visiting tourists, long term staying expats, and locals alike. ‚ô•Ô∏è thank you team Khao - So- I! Just a bit of an update/edit, I was feeling a bit hungry so I opted to add toppings (beef tendons and beef shank) worth it! good portions and they came in with the broth soup they were cooked in. Umami was over loaded.

I had an absolutely incredible experience here today and because of this I had to give it a five star review. The flavours were absolutely mind blowing - despite not liking spicy food (and it was very spicy for me) - the taste was so worth it. Plus, I just want to say that the staff are all fantastic and are happy to help with anything you need! Don‚Äôt miss this place if you are coming to Chiang Mai

Fantastic delicious and fun! We got the dumplings and beef with noodles and loved them. The dessert was a creamy and tangy lemon pudding. Great atmosphere, oh and try the butterfly pea lime juice drink! 10/10

The place gives off soft Ghibli vibes, calming atmosphere. Tried the Khao Soi and it was super comforting, creamy, not too spicy. Staff were really sweet and friendly, felt like being served by an old friend. especially the lady that i put the picture in here she was so nice. Definitely coming back next time I‚Äôm in Chiang Mai!

Amazing! Clean and the service was most definitely chefs kiss! Our server was phenomenal, kept it real while still creating a chill and professional environment. As someone who‚Äôs worked in the food service industry for years, that‚Äôs serious talent. The meal portions were perfect, slightly larger than I expected which was exactly what I love at an establishment. Attentive service all around from everyone. Would gladly recommend this place. Chefs are clearly quite skilled.

Real Khao Soi lovers know ‚Äî Khao So i is where it‚Äôs at. Bold flavors, silky noodles, and that signature crispy topping that hits just right. Chill atmosphere, amazing food ‚Äî what more could you ask for?

The food is delicious, the ice cream tastes great, and the latte is decent. I went on Saturday, and it was quite crowded. The tables are a bit too close to each other, but the lively atmosphere was nice. The best part, though, was the staff ‚Äî well-organized, service-minded, quick, and attentive. Truly impressive! There‚Äôs also convenient parking available.

Super delicious curry noodles with authentic Japanese d√©cor. The broth is rich and flavorful, and the noodles are perfectly cooked. Highly recommended for curry lovers! The waitress, ÈáëÊñØËò≠, was really nice and made our visit even more enjoyable."

My family order Khao Soi in Khao-So-i and fried rice with pork. The meat its very tender and so good to eat(not many meat like this) The fried rice so delicious, i eat it first and make me remind of my country (Even we are in Thai) The service is excelent, understanding (even i can speak Thai), delightful and so fast in serving (under 5 minutes) üëçüèªüëçüèª Hopefully one day i can visit here again

From the decor and ambience. To the presentation and taste of the food. You will not be disappointed. The staff is very friendly and attentive. This needs to be on your must try list for Chiang Mai. To top It off the ice cream is a great finishing dish to have before you leave.
Not sure how to categorize the restaurant. Perhaps Japanese-style fusion northern-Thai food would do.

Excellent food and atmosphere, prices are very reasonable for a simple but good main dish. Add-ons add up but being Thailand the price is still very reasonable. They do ask you to leave a review (and offer benefits for doing so) but I'm still happy rating this place 5/5.
Wonderful atmosphere! Khao-Soi with beef was so good, pork dumplings and Japanese Bun Milk delicious ü§§ highly recommend!
It‚Äôs a must try if you come to Chiang Mai. Everything is well served from staffs to food. The Kao Soi here is so delicious that I can‚Äôt stop eating once i start digging into my dish.

Had the dumpling with Khao Soi sauce and khao soi noodles with spare ribs and braised pork. The noodle with the ribs were great. Super tender ribs, noodle were chewy. Ordered their chrysanthemum tea as well which was refillable. Highly recommend their dumpling, generous filling and great taste. Definitely a recommended place if you are here in Chiang Mai

Hands down one of the best meal experiences I had in Chiang Mai. I ordered Pork Sausage Kao Soi, it was mind blowing. My wife also ordered chicken dry Khao Soi, it was good too. but I liked original soup version more.

Imagine Thai Khao Soi meets Japanese Ramen. This fusion style lets you experience a different type of khao soi. I went for the ultimate beef khao-soi, topped with a soft boiled egg and spare ribs, total (727 baht). 5 different types of beef elevated the dish together with the thick broth, it was totally worth it. Girlfriend went for the dry version with pork. It lets you experience a different feel of the dish. Similar to a yakisoba. Overall a great place to try a different type of khao soi.

Polite and helpful staffs, this is ‚Äúfusion style‚Äù delicious and worth to try. Their taste made for foreigner which is not too spicy. The taste is very different from the original Khao-Soi. Price relatively high but acceptable with service and ingredients. Great atmosphere and toilet quite clean. If you come at noon you can explore the tea bar and dessert. Parking not convenient as much as I expected.
We had a wonderful dining experience‚Äîthe service was impeccable, the food was superb, and the restaurant‚Äôs ambiance was stunning. A special thank you to Aoffy for the warm and attentive service!

Amazing ramen style khao soi! The broth is a little thick and has intense falvours, the meat is soft and goes well with the broth plus the steamed gyoza/ ‡πÄ‡∏Å‡πä‡∏¢‡∏ß is also really good as a side dish. üòã‚Ä¶ The service is very nice too, but beware it can get busy during lunch hours‚Ä¶

Khao Soi with amazing presentation! The place is cosy, the service is very friendly and welcoming. The staff explanation for food was also very clear and easy to understand. I tried their favorite menu here, the spice is strong and delicious! btw soup and side dishes are refillable for free!! I will come back again later. Thank you!!

Beautiful soul Aoffy gift us their fun Thai spirit and light-hearted curiosity about us. Aoffy also asked our desired spice level and showed us their menu's vegetarian and vegan options. We tried ALL vegan dishes with mild spice. So delicious is everything- steamed tofu salad, fried tofu with tangy sweet and sour chilli sauce, and inter-galactic Khao-Soi-I noodles with tofu. Follow their 1-2-3-4 card on how to put your main course together! You will remember the FUN!

Beautiful atmosphere delicious food. We highly recommend it was fun to visit. Just keep in mind that things are maybe a little spicier than most. Americans are familiar with but definitely tolerable and delicious. I personally am a wimp and I recommend the Khao soi with Wagyu stirfry.

I visited Kao So I for the second time, after trying it for the first time at Paragon. This branch is the original one, located in Chiang Mai. I love eating beef Khao Soi, so I ordered the same dish this time. The taste is consistent and up to standard. The service is good, and the restaurant has a Japanese-inspired atmosphere. Aside from Khao Soi, the must-try dish is still the fried tofu‚Äîcrispy on the outside, soft on the inside, and unmatched anywhere else.
Food is very good, the atmosphere is very welcoming and comfortable. Love the concept and design.
Really good spot, honestly one the best food/dish I have ever had (Khao so). Definitely would recommend it. The staff were super nice and super helpful as well.

The food tastes amazing and is worth the price. The Khao Soi is delicious, both the soup and dry versions, with a rich and flavorful broth. Side dishes can be requested for refills. The pork dumplings have thin wrappers and are packed with filling. Inside the restaurant, there‚Äôs also a coffee shop, and they even have private rooms for larger groups. The atmosphere and decor make you feel like you‚Äôre in Japan, capturing a truly Japanese vibe. This is another highly recommended place you should try!

So good!! I can‚Äôt handle food that‚Äôs too spicy, and the stir-fried noodles were perfect!! Loved that we could close stir-fried or soup! Atmosphere was incredible too! Friendly staff and clean space. 10/10 recommend!!!

Me and My BF went to Khao So I on last Tuesday because of the Tik Tok Reviews. The soup was incredibly rich and creamy, absolutely delicious. The meat was also very tender. It felt like we were eating Japanese cuisine even though we‚Äôre in Thailand. I also really loved the plating, it was beautifully presented. We especially liked the server who wore braces. She explained everything clearly and very charming and friendly. She even asked where we were from and made the effort to greet and chat with us a few times in our own language.üòç Plus the crispy pork is a must to try!!! üôåüèª

Khao-S≈ç-i is a popular restaurant in Chiang Mai, known for its fresh noodle Khao Soi. The menu features chicken, braised pork, and seafood options, along with creative dishes like Sai Ua Katsu. The food was incredible, service was amazing, atmosphere was great! Couldn‚Äôt say a bad word.All the food was amazing if ur not a fan of spicy food maybe it‚Äôs not for you, but if you are it‚Äôs a 10/10!!

Having really good time at restaurant with Mimi and aoffy üíïüòö totally worth the price of extra service and good foods here ! Do not skip this place when you come to Chiang Mai üòç
Best khao soi we had in Thailand. Delicious, fresh, really well done. And great service from Tanin/Tran :)

I had a great experience at Khao Soi I! The food was delicious, capturing the authentic flavors that Khao Soi is known for. The unique taste of Khao Soi is here... Cause there is a Thai & Japanese fusion Khao Soi... There are many other interesting menus too... The well designed & Bulit Japanese landscaping & Architecture are stunning... This is one of the must go place in Chiang Mai...

crazy good food, spicy and savory, with tasty drinks and delicious ice cream we got to have a taste of the khao soi soup before ordering it to see if it was too spicy for us which was really nice staff here is amazing and I‚Äôm really happy we found this place, it enhanced our Chiang Mai trip by a mile
Nice staffs and delicious northern food in modern style. MUST TRY IF YOU TRAVEL CHIANG MAI
The food was unbelievable good and tasted so fresh and rich!! Service was quick! Service was perfect friendly you name it!. 20/10

We are so look forward to try this shop as we read & watched so many recommendations about this. However, we are disappointed. Amazing food and a great atmosphere! Best service and we all had a very fun night here!

As an appetizer I ordered their signature dumplings and was very impressed. Each dumpling is filled with a lot of meat and the sauce has a nice tang to it. The presentation of the food is one of the most impressive parts and elevates the experience for me. There is also ice cream and a small cafe that‚Äôs part of the restaurant that I‚Äôll touch on later. Service: The service seems efficient and good overall. Despite being packed with people they really try to get to everyone in time. They are polite and are always moving, asking if you want refills or anything. The place is often crowded. It the turnover rate is quite good so the wait isn‚Äôt that long. Once someone leaves the waiters and waitresses are quick to clean it and call in the next customer. Facilities and other: the bathroom is clean. There is an ice cream soft serve shop and a cafe that are a part of the restaurant adding to the experience. The decor was very Japanese and creative! The wait staff showed us photos of the food on an iPad whilst we waited for a seat and gave some good recommendations on what to try.
Great khao soi - very rich broth and chicken and pork on top. Aoffi my server was so kind and attentive. A great lunch experience!

Khao Soi with a Japanese vibe - plating and decoration of the restaurant. Systematic way of getting a queue number, ordering and being seated once there is a vacant table. I love Thai tea! Everything is good

Really good fusion restaurant don't miss this place. I tried the Khao soi with beef the quality of beef and noodel is extraordinary. However, there is a limited place and table may be u have to prepare time for queue. No reservations only walk-in.
The best khao soi in Chiang Mai. Such a nice atmosphere. Great food Good ambience
Aoffy she accompany our family very well. And food is amazing üôèüèª

The food here is already yummy but I like the overall vibes, the place and how friendly and thoughtful staffs here are, they are well trained, we are super impressed by those all. Totally recommended but hard to get a parking and queue even on weekdays

A fantastic fusion of Japanese and Thai in architecture and food. Was great to have khao soi in a different way. I am used to traditional khao soi Gai but to have it de-constructed with wagu shin beef was a great change. Will come back for the traditional version soon as well üôèüòÉ
Phenomenal!!! Game kept us entertained and well informed while we waited for a table. Worth every penny!

I like their concept that is inspired by some Japanese Sobe shop or Ramen shop. Perhaps it wouldn't be strange if soba or ramen provide us here. Their khaosoi and side menus are delicious. Oustanding. Wagyu beef. Extra fried egg. Throw it all together and slurp away.
everything is really good here and the service and staff 5 star ü´∂üèªü´∂üèªü´∂üèªü´∂üèªü´∂üèªü´∂üèª i‚Äôll come back here when i visit chiang mai
Very good meal and very good service, thank you to Aoffy!
Wonderful service with great smiles and helpful workers, amazing food. Probably the best council I‚Äôve had in Northern! I highly recommend this wonderful place!

Absolutely love this place - great, delicious food and friendly staff. Don't miss out on their dumplings, they are super stuffed and flavour is amazing. Come early, or prepare to que in a long line - either way, it's worth it - amazing Khao Soi with good quality beef. Will be back next time in Chiang Mai.
The vibe of this place is pure magic. The red curry was fantastic but a bit spicy. Not too bad to handle. Free curry top-up.

A Taste of Northern Thai Perfection at Khao Soi I, Chiang Mai If you‚Äôre looking for an authentic culinary experience in Chiang Mai, Khao Soi I is a must-visit. Nestled in the heart of the city, this restaurant offers a warm and inviting atmosphere, complemented by its mouthwatering Northern Thai dishes. Their signature Khao Soi is simply perfection. The rich, creamy curry broth, tender chicken, and perfectly cooked noodles create a symphony of flavors that‚Äôs both comforting and exciting. The crispy noodles on top add a delightful crunch, and the accompanying lime, pickled mustard greens, and red onions provide the perfect balance to the dish. Beyond Khao Soi, the menu is a treasure trove of traditional delights. Their Sai Ua (Northern Thai sausage) is bursting with aromatic herbs and spices, and the Nam Prik Noom (green chili dip) is a flavorful dip that‚Äôs a testament to Northern Thai cuisine. The staff at Khao Soi I are incredibly friendly and attentive, ensuring every guest feels at home. The prices are also reasonable, making it accessible for travelers and locals alike. Khao Soi I isn‚Äôt just a meal; it‚Äôs an unforgettable journey into the heart of Northern Thailand‚Äôs rich culinary heritage. Highly recommended for anyone visiting Chiang Mai!

taste 4/5 place 4/5 service 5/5 overall 4.3/5 Khao soi or khao soy is a Chin Haw dish served in Laos and northern Thailand.The name means 'cut rice', although it is possible that it is simply a corruption of the Burmese word for noodles ‚Äì "khao sw√®" ‚Äì which may account for the variations. Traditionally, the dough for the rice noodles is spread out on a cloth stretched over boiling water. After steaming the large sheet noodle is then rolled and cut with scissors. Lao khao soi is traditionally made with hand sliced rice noodles in clear soup broth and topped with minced pork and tomato sauce. In some markets in Luang Namtha and Muang Sing vendors still hand cut the noodles. These traditionally cut noodles can also be found in several places in northern Thailand.

We had the chance to try the popular Khao Soi restaurant in Chiang Mai, Khao SO-I. Khao Soi is a traditional noodle dish from the northern part of Thailand. It consists of a noodle bowl with a rich curry sauce infused with herbs and curry paste, served with pickles, crispy noodles, and chili paste. Khao SO-I is a modern fusion of the flavors of Khao Soi with the artistry of Japanese Ramen. This restaurant has gained popularity in recent years, attracting many visitors to Chiang Mai eager to sample its special noodles. The restaurant is decorated in a Japanese style, with furniture and tools reflecting this theme. Food and drinks are also served in unique ceramic bowls, plates, and cups. We had the opportunity to try both the noodle bowl with curry sauce and the dry noodle plate, both of which were delicious! Highly recommended for noodle lovers. Yum!

Tijdens ons verblijf in Chiang Mai wilden we een keer echt goed uit eten, en Khao-S≈ç-i bleek de perfecte keuze. Dit restaurant heeft een luxe, moderne Japanse uitstraling, maar combineert dat moeiteloos met authentieke Noord-Thaise gerechten. Een geweldige mix van verfijning en traditie. Bij binnenkomst viel meteen de stijlvolle inrichting op: minimalistisch, warme houttinten en een ontspannen sfeer. De bediening was vriendelijk en professioneel, met veel kennis over de gerechten en drankjes. Geen overdreven formaliteit, gewoon oprecht gastvrij. De menukaart biedt een mooie balans tussen Japanse gerechten en lokale specialiteiten, waardoor je altijd iets bijzonders vindt. Ze gebruiken alleen verse, hoogwaardige ingredi√´nten, en dat proef je. We begonnen met een selectie Japanse hapjes ‚Äì prachtig gepresenteerd en verfijnd van smaak. Daarna kozen we hun khao soi, en die was echt top: een luxe versie van het klassieke gerecht, met romige curry, perfect gegaard vlees en knapperige noodles. Daarnaast waren de sushi en sashimi heerlijk vers en tot in detail verzorgd. De cocktails en sake maakten de ervaring compleet. En de prijs? In Nederland zou je hier drie keer zoveel voor betalen. In Chiang Mai eet je op hoog niveau voor minder dan een McDonald‚Äôs-menu thuis. Alles klopte: de sfeer, het eten, de service en vooral de prijs-kwaliteitverhouding. Khao-S≈ç-i is een must-visit in Chiang Mai!
